Delta State governor, Ifeanyi Okowa and his wife have tested positive for coronavirus. Okowa disclosed this on Wednesday on his verified Twitter handle. New swine flu with pandemic potential found in China He wrote, “My wife and I have tested positive for COVID-19. We are well and continuing with our isolation/medication. We thank you all for your continued prayers for us and our daughter.” My wife and I have tested positive for COVID-19. We are well and continuing with our isolation/medication. We thank you all for your continued prayers for us and our daughter. pic.twitter.com/NzBWB96Q91